Spain's second largest union, theWorkers Commissions, CC.OO, has voted against a general strikenext month to back wage demands and oppose the government'seconomic policies, a CC.OO spokesman said.    The proposal for a general strike was narrowly defeated ata meeting yesterday but union leaders voted instead for anational week of strike action beginning on April 3 and urgedtheir members to concentrate their protests on April 10.    The Socialist General Workers' Union, UGT, the country'sbiggest union, is against a general strike but has joinedforces with CC.OO. To demand real wage rises this year. Reuter&#3;